    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-09-10T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-09-10T13:00:00-05:00" n="177"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d177">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">800.8820/1352: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lane</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bogotá</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-09-10T13:00:00-05:00"
                            >September 10, 1943—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 4:41 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1598. In answer to the last paragraph of the Department’s 1135, September 9, 6
                    p.m., refer Department to my 1582, September 8, 1 p.m., which apparently crossed
                    Department’s telegram under <pb facs="0192" n="180" xml:id="pg_180"/>
                    acknowledgment. As stated in my 1582, President López stated to Connell and me
                    on September 8 that there is no objection on the part of the Colombian
                    Government to Alternative III.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lane</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
